1
00:00:04,004 --> 00:00:07,606
‎PREVIOUSLY ON <i>‎TATSUKI: TOO KIND FOR SCHOOL</i>

2
00:00:07,607 --> 00:00:10,409
<i>She said that she likes the color gold.</i>

3
00:00:10,410 --> 00:00:12,678
But I wonder if she said that
with her parents in mind.

4
00:00:12,679 --> 00:00:14,613
You need to go to cram school and study.

5
00:00:14,614 --> 00:00:16,349
She loves playing the piano.

6
00:00:18,985 --> 00:00:20,786
Mr. Tatsuki! It's about Nene…

7
00:00:20,787 --> 00:00:22,822
Thanks for coming.

8
00:00:24,024 --> 00:00:26,226
I don't know what to do anymore.

9
00:00:29,562 --> 00:00:31,830
Don't come in here! Go away!

10
00:00:31,831 --> 00:00:32,665
Sora!

11
00:00:33,833 --> 00:00:35,168
<i>Open the door, Sora!</i>

12
00:00:37,070 --> 00:00:38,238
I…

13
00:00:39,739 --> 00:00:41,106
don't know what to do either.

14
00:00:41,107 --> 00:00:42,375
What?

15
00:00:44,177 --> 00:00:45,011
But…

16
00:00:47,547 --> 00:00:48,848
I have to do something.

17
00:01:15,608 --> 00:01:16,609
I'm sorry.

18
00:01:21,781 --> 00:01:23,383
YUKANAI

19
00:01:52,979 --> 00:01:54,379
SPRING, 2019

20
00:01:54,380 --> 00:01:55,215
Hey,

21
00:01:55,949 --> 00:01:58,117
let's get going or we'll be late.

22
00:01:58,118 --> 00:01:58,952
Okay.

23
00:01:59,819 --> 00:02:01,321
- Here, this is for you.
- Oh?

24
00:02:02,021 --> 00:02:02,955
Wow.

25
00:02:02,956 --> 00:02:04,990
- It's pretty.
- Right?

26
00:02:04,991 --> 00:02:07,493
- Thanks.
- Okay, Dad, let's race.

27
00:02:07,494 --> 00:02:09,461
But I'll get sand in my shoes.

28
00:02:09,462 --> 00:02:10,896
Ready, start!

29
00:02:10,897 --> 00:02:11,798
Hey.

30
00:02:20,673 --> 00:02:22,007
Hold up!

31
00:02:22,008 --> 00:02:23,675
Oh no!

32
00:02:23,676 --> 00:02:24,511
Hey!

33
00:02:29,749 --> 00:02:33,286
SUMMER, 2023

34
00:02:46,799 --> 00:02:47,734
Hey…

35
00:02:48,835 --> 00:02:49,903
What is it?

36
00:02:50,770 --> 00:02:52,038
I want to take the entrance exam.

37
00:02:52,605 --> 00:02:54,072
- What?
- Entrance exam?

38
00:02:54,073 --> 00:02:56,543
Dad, you took it too, right?
I want to go to cram school.

39
00:02:57,710 --> 00:02:58,578
Oh…

40
00:02:59,078 --> 00:03:01,881
What do you think? It'll be tough
to start now, won't it?

41
00:03:04,717 --> 00:03:06,519
But I don't regret taking the exam.

42
00:03:07,453 --> 00:03:08,555
Okay.

43
00:03:11,257 --> 00:03:13,927
If you're willing to do your best,
we'll fully support you.

44
00:03:15,595 --> 00:03:16,429
I'll do my best.

45
00:03:18,264 --> 00:03:19,365
Okay.

46
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:22,501
Summer is the make-or-break period
for entrance exams.

47
00:03:22,502 --> 00:03:24,269
Train yourselves now

48
00:03:24,270 --> 00:03:27,607
so that you can give your all next summer.

49
00:03:28,174 --> 00:03:29,374
Yes, sir.

50
00:03:29,375 --> 00:03:31,777
All right, try solving

51
00:03:31,778 --> 00:03:33,478
the next question.

52
00:03:33,479 --> 00:03:35,981
Once you finish, move onto the next…

53
00:03:35,982 --> 00:03:38,418
154 DAYS UNTIL
THE JUNIOR HIGH SCHOOL ENTRANCE EXAMS

54
00:03:52,131 --> 00:03:53,199
Hey, there.

55
00:03:58,104 --> 00:03:58,938
What's the matter?

56
00:04:00,673 --> 00:04:02,975
I barely passed the mock exam.

57
00:04:02,976 --> 00:04:03,843
What?

58
00:04:05,712 --> 00:04:07,614
GRADE - C

59
00:04:09,015 --> 00:04:10,817
There's still time, so keep at it.

60
00:04:14,587 --> 00:04:15,688
I'm tired.

61
00:04:16,556 --> 00:04:17,957
You're the one who wanted to do this.

62
00:04:19,692 --> 00:04:20,927
Yeah, but…

63
00:04:22,829 --> 00:04:26,399
Once you get accepted into a school,
you can have all the fun you want.

64
00:04:29,369 --> 00:04:30,570
Yeah.

65
00:04:42,215 --> 00:04:44,550
HAPPY NEW YEAR

66
00:04:49,389 --> 00:04:51,823
TOEI GAKUEN JUNIOR HIGH SCHOOL
ENTRANCE EXAM RESULTS

67
00:04:51,824 --> 00:04:54,060
USERNAME
PASSWORD

68
00:04:56,262 --> 00:04:57,629
Hurry up.

69
00:04:57,630 --> 00:04:58,698
Hold on…

70
00:05:08,341 --> 00:05:09,574
CONGRATULATIONS, YOU PASSED

71
00:05:09,575 --> 00:05:11,576
- All right!
- Wow!

72
00:05:11,577 --> 00:05:13,045
- I did it!
- Congrats!

73
00:05:13,046 --> 00:05:14,414
I did it!

74
00:05:22,488 --> 00:05:24,757
I guess Sora won't be
walking with us anymore, huh?

75
00:05:25,692 --> 00:05:27,326
Since he's in junior high now.

76
00:05:27,327 --> 00:05:28,861
And his school is far from here.

77
00:05:30,596 --> 00:05:31,764
- Later.
- Yeah.

78
00:05:37,403 --> 00:05:41,607
MID-TERM EXAM

79
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:15,408
What are you doing?

80
00:06:17,443 --> 00:06:18,910
The concept this time

81
00:06:18,911 --> 00:06:21,213
is a fountain pen that doesn't
interrupt the thought process.

82
00:06:21,214 --> 00:06:22,147
YU

83
00:06:22,148 --> 00:06:23,216
We branded this fountain pen,

84
00:06:24,016 --> 00:06:24,851
um…

85
00:06:27,186 --> 00:06:31,057
not solely for writing, but to accompany
you during periods of deep contemplation.

86
00:06:32,392 --> 00:06:33,492
Hello?

87
00:06:33,493 --> 00:06:35,360
Yeah?

88
00:06:35,361 --> 00:06:36,195
What?

89
00:06:37,597 --> 00:06:39,499
What? He was caught cheating?

90
00:06:41,167 --> 00:06:42,969
Why did you cheat, of all things?

91
00:06:45,304 --> 00:06:47,740
Is it hard to keep up with your studies?

92
00:06:53,613 --> 00:06:55,848
You worked so hard to get in,
so why do something so stupid?

93
00:06:57,950 --> 00:06:58,785
Hey,

94
00:07:00,953 --> 00:07:01,988
say something.

95
00:07:07,427 --> 00:07:08,461
Hey, Sora.

96
00:07:21,908 --> 00:07:22,975
Sora.

97
00:07:37,390 --> 00:07:38,424
SHUT UP

98
00:08:09,589 --> 00:08:11,656
Since today is the 2nd of the month,

99
00:08:11,657 --> 00:08:14,260
the second person on roll call
will solve this one. Which is…

100
00:08:17,029 --> 00:08:18,330
Here.

101
00:08:18,331 --> 00:08:20,199
Okay, Ukita. Come up here.

102
00:08:36,482 --> 00:08:39,752
Let's break it down once,
like we did with the example equation.

103
00:08:45,925 --> 00:08:48,394
- Look at your cheat sheet.
- That's too harsh.

104
00:08:50,196 --> 00:08:52,931
- He'll never be able to solve that.
- Yeah, for sure.

105
00:08:52,932 --> 00:08:54,267
Look, he's frozen.

106
00:08:55,401 --> 00:08:56,769
You can go back to your seat.

107
00:09:02,642 --> 00:09:03,542
- Hey!
- Ukita!

108
00:09:03,543 --> 00:09:06,111
- You wanna fight?
- Ukita!

109
00:09:06,112 --> 00:09:07,279
Stop it!

110
00:09:07,280 --> 00:09:08,980
Calm down, Ukita!

111
00:09:08,981 --> 00:09:10,182
Hey!

112
00:09:13,586 --> 00:09:14,819
- Hey.
- Yeah?

113
00:09:14,820 --> 00:09:17,422
Sora is holed up in his room
and won't come out.

114
00:09:17,423 --> 00:09:18,490
Why?

115
00:09:18,491 --> 00:09:20,860
Apparently, he had a fight
with a friend at school yesterday.

116
00:09:21,928 --> 00:09:23,329
That's it?

117
00:09:25,932 --> 00:09:27,767
Hey, why aren't you coming out?

118
00:09:30,336 --> 00:09:34,272
Sora, hiding out like that
isn't going to solve anything, you know?

119
00:09:34,273 --> 00:09:36,208
Hey, let's talk together.

120
00:09:37,743 --> 00:09:38,578
Are you listening?

121
00:09:39,879 --> 00:09:42,514
- Sora.
- That's enough. Go to work.

122
00:09:42,515 --> 00:09:44,583
Open the door.

123
00:09:44,584 --> 00:09:45,418
Sora.

124
00:09:47,453 --> 00:09:49,255
- Come out here.
- I don't want to!

125
00:09:50,156 --> 00:09:52,425
Stop it, that's enough. Just stop!

126
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:55,628
Sora!

127
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:01,600
TWO WEEKS LATER

128
00:10:01,601 --> 00:10:02,501
What about work?

129
00:10:04,470 --> 00:10:06,172
I'll take the day off again.

130
00:10:08,641 --> 00:10:09,909
Okay, thanks.

131
00:10:12,044 --> 00:10:13,846
How long is this going to continue?

132
00:10:19,585 --> 00:10:20,853
I'll think of something.

133
00:10:23,155 --> 00:10:24,023
Bye.

134
00:10:34,867 --> 00:10:36,401
ANY CHILD WITH SCHOOL REFUSAL CAN RETURN
TO SCHOOL - GUARANTEED 97% SUCCESS!

135
00:10:36,402 --> 00:10:39,405
"REVIVAL!" A SPECIALIZED SUPPORT SERVICE
FOR SCHOOL REFUSAL

136
00:10:43,242 --> 00:10:44,810
When did his school refusal begin?

137
00:10:45,378 --> 00:10:47,713
I'm not sure yet
if it's exactly school refusal,

138
00:10:48,247 --> 00:10:49,848
but it started about two weeks ago.

139
00:10:49,849 --> 00:10:51,684
Two weeks, I see.

140
00:10:53,886 --> 00:10:55,021
It's not too late.

141
00:10:56,022 --> 00:10:56,889
Really?

142
00:10:58,157 --> 00:10:59,525
It all started…

143
00:11:00,726 --> 00:11:01,727
with the cheating?

144
00:11:02,528 --> 00:11:03,428
I believe so.

145
00:11:03,429 --> 00:11:05,563
That made it difficult for him
to go to school?

146
00:11:05,564 --> 00:11:06,632
Yes.

147
00:11:08,267 --> 00:11:11,670
If you follow our program as directed,

148
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:15,607
he should be able to return to school
in approximately three to four weeks.

149
00:11:15,608 --> 00:11:17,143
Is that right?

150
00:11:20,012 --> 00:11:24,250
Children are not to be blamed
for experiencing school refusal.

151
00:11:26,619 --> 00:11:29,722
In other words,
the ones who need to change

152
00:11:30,322 --> 00:11:31,657
are the parents.

153
00:11:42,234 --> 00:11:43,235
What is it?

154
00:11:46,272 --> 00:11:48,574
- What are you doing?
- You can have them if you go to school.

155
00:11:49,141 --> 00:11:50,443
What?

156
00:11:51,010 --> 00:11:52,311
Give it back to me.

157
00:12:08,227 --> 00:12:11,596
IT ALL STARTS WITH PARENTS'
CHANGING THEIR MINDSET

158
00:12:11,597 --> 00:12:13,065
The parents' mindset…

159
00:12:20,639 --> 00:12:22,808
Aren't you taking this a bit too far?

160
00:12:23,876 --> 00:12:26,178
It's all because
you keep spoiling him like that.

161
00:12:26,846 --> 00:12:28,647
What? So it's my fault?

162
00:12:30,082 --> 00:12:32,885
If he has his phone and games,
he won't feel the need to leave his room.

163
00:12:34,887 --> 00:12:37,589
Hey, is this company really trustworthy?

164
00:12:37,590 --> 00:12:39,324
We, the parents, need to make changes.

165
00:12:39,325 --> 00:12:40,426
Are you listening to me?

166
00:12:41,327 --> 00:12:43,629
Starting tomorrow,
I'll set a routine schedule for him.

167
00:12:53,405 --> 00:12:54,306
Wake up.

168
00:12:58,477 --> 00:13:00,646
- Get up.
- Stop it.

169
00:13:03,082 --> 00:13:04,150
Hurry up.

170
00:13:08,320 --> 00:13:09,188
Listen up, Sora.

171
00:13:09,755 --> 00:13:14,026
You're capable of hard work, and you can
do anything if you put your mind to it.

172
00:13:15,127 --> 00:13:15,961
Right?

173
00:13:17,363 --> 00:13:18,297
So

174
00:13:18,898 --> 00:13:21,100
let's get you back on a routine schedule.

175
00:13:24,503 --> 00:13:25,504
My phone…

176
00:13:26,405 --> 00:13:29,040
You don't need your smartphone,
games, or comics.

177
00:13:29,041 --> 00:13:30,843
If you're not going to school,
study at home.

178
00:13:31,544 --> 00:13:32,378
Got it?

179
00:13:36,882 --> 00:13:39,351
You can have it back
once you go to school.

180
00:13:48,360 --> 00:13:50,662
Crying won't solve anything.

181
00:13:50,663 --> 00:13:51,729
Stop being so harsh.

182
00:13:51,730 --> 00:13:53,165
Do what needs to be done.

183
00:13:56,669 --> 00:13:57,735
Sora.

184
00:13:57,736 --> 00:13:59,971
Put away your own dishes.

185
00:13:59,972 --> 00:14:00,940
Hey, Sora!

186
00:14:08,647 --> 00:14:10,114
OFFER PRAISE,
ESTABLISH A PROPER HOME ENVIRONMENT,

187
00:14:10,115 --> 00:14:11,217
ENCOURAGE INDEPENDENCE, RETURN TO SCHOOL

188
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:19,151
Sora?

189
00:15:20,252 --> 00:15:21,853
You're going to school?

190
00:15:21,854 --> 00:15:23,022
I'll be off.

191
00:15:27,993 --> 00:15:30,629
- Hey, Sora went to school!
- What?

192
00:15:31,430 --> 00:15:33,299
Really?

193
00:15:35,834 --> 00:15:36,735
I'm glad.

194
00:16:00,659 --> 00:16:02,560
Didn't we have art class today?

195
00:16:02,561 --> 00:16:04,195
Oh, did we? Let's hurry.

196
00:16:04,196 --> 00:16:05,064
I'll go too.

197
00:16:10,869 --> 00:16:12,137
ART

198
00:16:18,744 --> 00:16:22,013
All right everyone, start sketching.

199
00:16:22,014 --> 00:16:23,315
Okay.

200
00:17:04,056 --> 00:17:04,990
Sora?

201
00:17:06,258 --> 00:17:07,259
What are you doing?

202
00:17:12,364 --> 00:17:15,968
Dad told you
that you can't use your phone, right?

203
00:17:17,736 --> 00:17:19,038
I went to school, so it's fine.

204
00:17:20,472 --> 00:17:21,640
Sora…

205
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:24,475
Give it to me. It's all right.

206
00:17:24,476 --> 00:17:25,811
Just give it back to me.

207
00:17:26,378 --> 00:17:27,513
Sora.

208
00:17:42,828 --> 00:17:43,695
Give it back.

209
00:17:45,931 --> 00:17:46,832
Give it back!

210
00:18:05,551 --> 00:18:06,785
I'm home.

211
00:18:16,495 --> 00:18:17,496
What?

212
00:18:20,499 --> 00:18:21,333
What happened?

213
00:18:24,536 --> 00:18:25,671
Sora.

214
00:18:29,475 --> 00:18:30,642
Hey, Sora!

215
00:18:32,544 --> 00:18:34,312
- Sora!
- Don't come in here!

216
00:18:34,313 --> 00:18:35,781
Go away!

217
00:18:39,852 --> 00:18:40,886
Why…

218
00:18:43,155 --> 00:18:45,491
He was never the type
to do something like this.

219
00:18:46,992 --> 00:18:49,561
- Open the door, Sora.
- Shut up!

220
00:19:00,372 --> 00:19:01,507
Hey Sora.

221
00:19:03,509 --> 00:19:04,376
Open the door.

222
00:19:17,022 --> 00:19:18,122
MUNICIPAL GENERAL MEDICAL CENTER

223
00:19:18,123 --> 00:19:19,657
Are you scolding him harshly,

224
00:19:19,658 --> 00:19:23,261
or doing anything that might
make him feel cornered?

225
00:19:23,262 --> 00:19:24,163
Well,

226
00:19:25,164 --> 00:19:27,032
I am, of course, a little strict with him,

227
00:19:27,766 --> 00:19:29,835
but it’s because I want him
to lead a disciplined life.

228
00:19:31,069 --> 00:19:35,106
Right now, he might be feeling
intense stress at both school and home

229
00:19:35,107 --> 00:19:37,609
to the point where he feels
he has nowhere left to turn.

230
00:19:39,845 --> 00:19:41,046
For now, please prioritize

231
00:19:41,647 --> 00:19:43,715
- your child's feelings.
- Huh?

232
00:19:44,483 --> 00:19:45,317
That's really okay?

233
00:19:45,884 --> 00:19:48,220
- His school refusal will never be solved--
- Sir.

234
00:19:49,054 --> 00:19:50,856
Focus on giving the help he needs
right now.

235
00:19:53,592 --> 00:19:56,595
Then what do you suggest I do right now?

236
00:19:59,598 --> 00:20:00,866
Let's see.

237
00:20:02,801 --> 00:20:05,804
How about I introduce you
to a certified psychologist?

238
00:20:08,273 --> 00:20:09,674
No, thank you.

239
00:20:09,675 --> 00:20:11,576
EXAM ROOM 2

240
00:20:11,577 --> 00:20:12,610
I'll go home on my own.

241
00:20:12,611 --> 00:20:13,812
Sora.

242
00:20:19,518 --> 00:20:21,420
I'm sorry. Sorry.

243
00:20:22,321 --> 00:20:24,289
No worries. Please go after him.

244
00:20:25,023 --> 00:20:26,258
Thanks for helping.

245
00:20:27,459 --> 00:20:28,727
I understand how you feel.

246
00:20:29,528 --> 00:20:32,798
My son also went through a terrible
rebellious phase back in the day.

247
00:20:36,168 --> 00:20:38,303
If you have time,
please come to this event.

248
00:20:38,804 --> 00:20:41,272
LET'S TRY ART THERAPY!

249
00:20:41,273 --> 00:20:43,375
- I see.
- I'll be going now. Bye.

250
00:20:50,616 --> 00:20:53,952
FINDING YOUR INNER SELF
THROUGH ART THERAPY

251
00:20:58,090 --> 00:20:58,924
Where were you?

252
00:21:02,094 --> 00:21:04,696
Am I sick?

253
00:21:05,430 --> 00:21:07,633
What do you mean?

254
00:21:08,567 --> 00:21:09,801
I was at the hospital.

255
00:21:10,836 --> 00:21:11,670
What?

256
00:21:16,341 --> 00:21:18,376
Why did you take him to the hospital?

257
00:21:18,377 --> 00:21:19,977
We went to a psychosomatic clinic.

258
00:21:19,978 --> 00:21:22,281
I thought they might be able to figure out
what caused this.

259
00:21:26,818 --> 00:21:27,686
Why?

260
00:21:28,220 --> 00:21:29,621
What do you mean by "why"?

261
00:21:31,256 --> 00:21:32,757
You didn't even consult with me,

262
00:21:32,758 --> 00:21:34,558
and paid money to some shady company,

263
00:21:34,559 --> 00:21:36,794
- and took him to a hospital--
- It's to help Sora.

264
00:21:36,795 --> 00:21:38,230
It's not helping him at all!

265
00:21:40,265 --> 00:21:42,167
Can't you see that he's getting worse?

266
00:21:46,171 --> 00:21:48,573
I can't take this anymore.

267
00:21:59,851 --> 00:22:01,987
I want you to stay away from him.

268
00:22:03,922 --> 00:22:05,957
- What?
- I'm begging you.

269
00:22:23,642 --> 00:22:26,078
FROM YU

270
00:22:34,353 --> 00:22:36,855
DIVORCE FORM

271
00:22:42,394 --> 00:22:43,795
YU UKITA

272
00:23:28,206 --> 00:23:31,143
You're showing signs of depression.

273
00:23:33,145 --> 00:23:34,980
Please do not overexert yourself at work,

274
00:23:35,514 --> 00:23:37,681
and try to eliminate
environmental stressors

275
00:23:37,682 --> 00:23:38,817
as much as possible.

276
00:23:41,286 --> 00:23:43,622
Do you have any family members
that can provide support?

277
00:23:48,927 --> 00:23:49,761
No.

278
00:23:57,302 --> 00:23:59,837
I haven't drawn in so long,
I'm a little nervous.

279
00:23:59,838 --> 00:24:01,338
Yeah, it's a bit nerve-wracking.

280
00:24:01,339 --> 00:24:03,040
Thank you for coming today.

281
00:24:03,041 --> 00:24:05,309
It's so nostalgic.

282
00:24:05,310 --> 00:24:06,611
This was drawn using crayons.

283
00:24:07,846 --> 00:24:08,747
Welcome.

284
00:24:09,815 --> 00:24:10,714
Please come inside.

285
00:24:10,715 --> 00:24:12,250
No, I'm all right.

286
00:24:13,852 --> 00:24:15,053
Please come in.

287
00:24:16,655 --> 00:24:20,591
You may not be very familiar
with the concept of art therapy,

288
00:24:20,592 --> 00:24:22,293
but it is a therapeutic approach

289
00:24:22,294 --> 00:24:25,996
in which you engage with your inner self
and sort through your feelings

290
00:24:25,997 --> 00:24:28,266
with activities such as drawing
or working with clay.

291
00:24:29,468 --> 00:24:30,968
And please be rest assured,

292
00:24:30,969 --> 00:24:33,705
despite the name,
you do not need any artistic skills.

293
00:24:34,573 --> 00:24:35,807
Are you relieved?

294
00:24:36,942 --> 00:24:40,878
Today, please draw a landscape
that is memorable to you,

295
00:24:40,879 --> 00:24:42,013
or perhaps the sky.

296
00:24:42,848 --> 00:24:44,148
Please begin.

297
00:24:44,149 --> 00:24:46,217
Please relax and enjoy drawing.

298
00:24:46,218 --> 00:24:48,353
- What should I draw?
- Enjoy.

299
00:25:01,366 --> 00:25:03,468
You painted a view of the sky by the sea.

300
00:25:04,636 --> 00:25:05,604
Yes.

301
00:25:07,405 --> 00:25:08,907
What kind of memories do you have here?

302
00:25:10,609 --> 00:25:13,111
There's no specific "memory," but…

303
00:25:29,194 --> 00:25:30,929
Are these footprints?

304
00:25:33,698 --> 00:25:34,599
Yes.

305
00:25:37,536 --> 00:25:39,371
You must've walked quite a distance.

306
00:25:47,279 --> 00:25:49,214
I really felt like I was doing my best,

307
00:25:51,416 --> 00:25:53,351
but it seems
I was just spinning my wheels…

308
00:25:55,587 --> 00:25:58,256
Even the things I did
with my son's best interests at heart

309
00:25:59,524 --> 00:26:00,692
turned out to be wrong.

310
00:26:06,097 --> 00:26:07,098
I'm sorry.

311
00:26:07,866 --> 00:26:09,834
No need to apologize.

312
00:26:11,102 --> 00:26:12,637
You can talk about anything here.

313
00:26:20,278 --> 00:26:21,413
What's the matter?

314
00:26:28,954 --> 00:26:30,355
Both family and work

315
00:26:31,456 --> 00:26:33,191
can be lost in an instant.

316
00:26:39,264 --> 00:26:40,165
This…

317
00:26:43,068 --> 00:26:45,570
is scenery I'll never get to see
ever again.

318
00:27:05,423 --> 00:27:06,357
I'm sorry.

319
00:27:06,358 --> 00:27:08,560
- No worries.
- Thanks.

320
00:27:11,229 --> 00:27:14,131
Do you draw often, Mr. Tatsuki?

321
00:27:14,132 --> 00:27:17,001
Yes. I studied design at university.

322
00:27:17,002 --> 00:27:20,105
No wonder you're so good.

323
00:27:20,639 --> 00:27:22,072
Do you draw too?

324
00:27:22,073 --> 00:27:24,274
No, I specialize in psychology

325
00:27:24,275 --> 00:27:25,977
and I'm terrible at drawing.

326
00:27:27,078 --> 00:27:29,748
But art is very useful
when trying to confront oneself.

327
00:27:31,950 --> 00:27:33,084
I see.

328
00:27:36,488 --> 00:27:38,857
- Mr. Tatsuki.
- Yes?

329
00:27:39,424 --> 00:27:40,892
Do you have time after this?

330
00:27:41,993 --> 00:27:42,893
What?

331
00:27:42,894 --> 00:27:44,528
YUKANAI

332
00:27:44,529 --> 00:27:45,596
NOW ACCEPTING NEW STUDENTS

333
00:27:45,597 --> 00:27:47,164
This way. Please come in.

334
00:27:47,165 --> 00:27:48,332
Thank you.

335
00:27:48,333 --> 00:27:49,467
Hey everyone.

336
00:27:50,035 --> 00:27:52,170
- Hello.
- Hello.

337
00:27:53,605 --> 00:27:56,807
This is the alternative school
that I founded.

338
00:27:56,808 --> 00:27:58,209
- Alternative school?
- Yes.

339
00:27:58,877 --> 00:28:02,480
I wanted to create a safe space
for children who,

340
00:28:03,181 --> 00:28:04,282
for various reasons,

341
00:28:04,849 --> 00:28:06,184
find it hard to attend school.

342
00:28:07,252 --> 00:28:08,420
I see.

343
00:28:09,587 --> 00:28:10,788
Oh, you're drawing.

344
00:28:10,789 --> 00:28:12,723
Look at this.

345
00:28:12,724 --> 00:28:14,158
You're so good.

346
00:28:14,159 --> 00:28:15,793
- Really?
- Yeah.

347
00:28:15,794 --> 00:28:17,895
- Look.
- How cute.

348
00:28:17,896 --> 00:28:20,297
- Look at this.
- Isn't this funny?

349
00:28:20,298 --> 00:28:21,599
That's cute.

350
00:28:22,767 --> 00:28:24,102
This way.

351
00:28:24,736 --> 00:28:25,570
Okay.

352
00:28:26,604 --> 00:28:28,772
I'm thinking it'd be nice
to offer art therapy here

353
00:28:28,773 --> 00:28:30,709
as a way to tie it in
with my own research.

354
00:28:31,609 --> 00:28:32,677
I see.

355
00:28:33,478 --> 00:28:34,846
Would you like to work here with me?

356
00:28:35,847 --> 00:28:36,914
What?

357
00:28:36,915 --> 00:28:38,382
You quit your other job, right?

358
00:28:38,383 --> 00:28:40,285
Yeah, but…

359
00:28:41,052 --> 00:28:44,354
You lost everything
triggered by the issue of school refusal,

360
00:28:44,355 --> 00:28:47,191
and now you're at rock bottom, aren't you?

361
00:28:47,192 --> 00:28:48,660
You're so brutally honest.

362
00:28:49,694 --> 00:28:50,894
Are you good with games?

363
00:28:50,895 --> 00:28:52,463
Not really.

364
00:28:52,464 --> 00:28:54,832
But you can draw.

365
00:28:54,833 --> 00:28:56,668
- I think you're suitable for this job.
- Um…

366
00:28:58,303 --> 00:29:00,238
I'm very thankful for the offer,

367
00:29:00,972 --> 00:29:02,707
but why me, we've only just met?

368
00:29:05,844 --> 00:29:06,845
My intuition, I guess.

369
00:29:09,114 --> 00:29:09,948
What?

370
00:29:10,915 --> 00:29:13,016
- I'm first.
- No, it's me.

371
00:29:13,017 --> 00:29:14,785
- It's my turn.
- No, it's me.

372
00:29:14,786 --> 00:29:15,886
- Hey, hey.
- Let go.

373
00:29:15,887 --> 00:29:18,122
You have to take turns.

374
00:29:18,123 --> 00:29:19,823
- Or someone will get hurt.
- It's my turn.

375
00:29:19,824 --> 00:29:21,626
Wow, that was consecutive.

376
00:29:22,293 --> 00:29:23,727
Seiryu,

377
00:29:23,728 --> 00:29:26,029
clean up after yourself.
Don't leave things out.

378
00:29:26,030 --> 00:29:27,297
I didn't do that.

379
00:29:27,298 --> 00:29:28,199
Huh?

380
00:29:36,541 --> 00:29:39,444
Who wants to play in the courtyard?

381
00:29:42,113 --> 00:29:44,047
- So, about this…
- Yeah?

382
00:29:44,048 --> 00:29:45,250
Haruhi, Kurumi, wanna play?

383
00:29:46,050 --> 00:29:48,085
- No, I'm okay.
- No thanks.

384
00:29:48,086 --> 00:29:51,655
- Soya, let's play <i>Mario Party</i>.
- You're not going to play soccer?

385
00:29:51,656 --> 00:29:53,123
No, Mr. Tatsuki is scary.

386
00:29:53,124 --> 00:29:54,725
- Oh…
- Let's play games.

387
00:29:54,726 --> 00:29:56,927
- Okay…
- I wanna play with you too.

388
00:29:56,928 --> 00:29:58,930
Oh no, hold on.

389
00:29:59,764 --> 00:30:01,698
That was close.

390
00:30:01,699 --> 00:30:02,634
Watch out!

391
00:30:14,479 --> 00:30:16,481
Mr. Tatsuki, are you all right?

392
00:30:24,455 --> 00:30:26,557
Oh my god.

393
00:30:26,558 --> 00:30:28,493
It's Café-Au-Lait Man!

394
00:30:29,561 --> 00:30:30,994
No, he's a zombie.

395
00:30:30,995 --> 00:30:33,498
You're right. He's a zombie.

396
00:30:35,133 --> 00:30:38,168
- Café-Au-Lait Zombie.
- Hey, zombie.

397
00:30:38,169 --> 00:30:44,641
A zombie! A zombie!

398
00:30:44,642 --> 00:30:46,211
Who are you calling a zombie?

399
00:30:53,518 --> 00:30:55,320
The zombie is here.

400
00:31:08,733 --> 00:31:11,034
Peter Piper picked a peck
of pickled peppers…

401
00:31:11,035 --> 00:31:13,171
Good morning.

402
00:31:13,972 --> 00:31:14,806
What the…?

403
00:31:15,406 --> 00:31:17,708
What?

404
00:31:17,709 --> 00:31:18,642
What do you think?

405
00:31:18,643 --> 00:31:19,911
Your hair color changed.

406
00:31:20,511 --> 00:31:21,812
A makeover? That's nice.

407
00:31:21,813 --> 00:31:23,647
You look like Super Saiyan.

408
00:31:23,648 --> 00:31:25,782
- You're Super Saiyan!
- It's gross.

409
00:31:25,783 --> 00:31:27,050
Who said it was gross?

410
00:31:27,051 --> 00:31:29,686
The look suits you.

411
00:31:29,687 --> 00:31:31,656
You look like a nice fairy.

412
00:31:32,523 --> 00:31:33,757
Thank you.

413
00:31:33,758 --> 00:31:35,626
- Mr. Tatsuki.
- Yeah?

414
00:31:35,627 --> 00:31:36,895
I want to draw.

415
00:31:37,595 --> 00:31:38,528
Okay.

416
00:31:38,529 --> 00:31:42,299
But from now on,
you can just call me Tatsuki.

417
00:31:42,300 --> 00:31:45,402
- Tatsuki, can we use the atelier?
- Of course.

418
00:31:45,403 --> 00:31:47,838
- Let's go, everyone!
- Yeah.

419
00:31:47,839 --> 00:31:49,640
Wait for me.

420
00:31:49,641 --> 00:31:51,175
- Tatsuki.
- Yeah?

421
00:31:52,377 --> 00:31:53,211
Not bad.

422
00:31:54,579 --> 00:31:55,479
Shut up.

423
00:31:55,480 --> 00:31:57,748
- Not bad.
- Not bad.

424
00:31:57,749 --> 00:31:59,283
Not bad.

425
00:31:59,284 --> 00:32:01,752
- Not bad.
- Enough already.

426
00:32:01,753 --> 00:32:04,188
YUKANAI

427
00:32:18,803 --> 00:32:22,774
YU

428
00:32:25,643 --> 00:32:27,377
- Hello?
<i>- Tatsuki…</i>

429
00:32:27,378 --> 00:32:28,913
Sora… Sora…

430
00:32:30,348 --> 00:32:31,281
What about Sora?

431
00:32:31,282 --> 00:32:33,017
Sora jumped.

432
00:32:34,319 --> 00:32:35,153
What?

433
00:33:11,756 --> 00:33:12,657
Hey there.

434
00:33:13,958 --> 00:33:15,360
Hello.

435
00:33:16,594 --> 00:33:18,963
I heard that Nene's situation
isn't looking good?

436
00:33:19,697 --> 00:33:20,531
Yeah.

437
00:33:25,236 --> 00:33:27,004
<i>Is it okay if her grades keep dropping?</i>

438
00:33:27,005 --> 00:33:28,739
You need to go to cram school and study.

439
00:33:28,740 --> 00:33:30,574
She loves playing the piano.

440
00:33:30,575 --> 00:33:32,109
I hate playing the piano.

441
00:33:32,110 --> 00:33:34,544
- Then why didn't you say so?
- There's no way I could.

442
00:33:34,545 --> 00:33:35,979
If I do,

443
00:33:35,980 --> 00:33:38,282
you and Dad will start fighting again.

444
00:33:40,118 --> 00:33:43,054
<i>I don't want things
to turn out like it did with Sora.</i>

445
00:33:44,789 --> 00:33:45,889
But I don't know what to do.

446
00:33:45,890 --> 00:33:47,725
How were her parents doing?

447
00:33:50,028 --> 00:33:51,496
They're very similar

448
00:33:52,096 --> 00:33:53,498
to how I was back then.

449
00:33:55,133 --> 00:33:57,000
As if their expectations and hopes

450
00:33:57,001 --> 00:33:58,769
for their child have gone awry,

451
00:33:58,770 --> 00:34:00,972
trapping them in a vicious cycle.

452
00:34:02,740 --> 00:34:03,641
I see.

453
00:34:04,642 --> 00:34:06,778
I went to the door of her room,

454
00:34:10,181 --> 00:34:12,383
<i>but I couldn't do anything,
and I just left.</i>

455
00:34:18,389 --> 00:34:20,558
Why don't we invite her parents here?

456
00:34:21,859 --> 00:34:23,127
Invite them here?

457
00:34:24,228 --> 00:34:25,830
There's some art therapy
I want to try out.

458
00:34:26,464 --> 00:34:28,132
Of course, you’ll be doing it too.

459
00:34:34,439 --> 00:34:35,306
This way, please.

460
00:34:37,708 --> 00:34:38,543
Hello.

461
00:34:39,110 --> 00:34:41,379
I'm Mikumo, the representative at Yukanai.

462
00:34:43,314 --> 00:34:45,716
- Thank you for your help.
- Thank you for coming.

463
00:34:47,852 --> 00:34:49,620
Why were we called here today?

464
00:34:50,621 --> 00:34:53,256
We're all concerned about Nene,

465
00:34:53,257 --> 00:34:54,691
but we can only imagine

466
00:34:54,692 --> 00:34:57,128
that it's been a tremendous burden
on you two as well.

467
00:34:57,862 --> 00:35:01,899
So we wanted to have you
spend some time relaxing today.

468
00:35:03,101 --> 00:35:05,503
So we prepared this.

469
00:35:06,704 --> 00:35:07,604
Please sit down.

470
00:35:07,605 --> 00:35:08,739
Yes, please.

471
00:35:09,440 --> 00:35:10,408
Thank you.

472
00:35:13,411 --> 00:35:16,714
Does this have anything to do with Nene?

473
00:35:17,448 --> 00:35:18,282
Yes.

474
00:35:19,884 --> 00:35:21,752
Please bear with us
for just a little while.

475
00:35:23,721 --> 00:35:27,724
This is a traditional dyeing
and transfer technique

476
00:35:27,725 --> 00:35:29,960
called <i>suminagashi</i>.

477
00:35:29,961 --> 00:35:32,196
I'll start by showing you how it's done.

478
00:35:33,464 --> 00:35:34,932
Start by dropping

479
00:35:35,967 --> 00:35:38,002
sumi ink onto the surface of the water.

480
00:35:40,972 --> 00:35:43,040
And this is oil.

481
00:35:44,375 --> 00:35:47,245
Mix the oil with the sumi ink.

482
00:35:49,080 --> 00:35:51,182
You can swirl the sumi ink like this.

483
00:35:52,049 --> 00:35:53,450
Once you're done with that,

484
00:35:53,451 --> 00:35:56,554
you can gently shake
the surface of the water,

485
00:35:57,522 --> 00:35:59,657
or you can blow on it as well.

486
00:36:03,794 --> 00:36:04,761
Oh no,

487
00:36:04,762 --> 00:36:07,063
it's not turning out the way I imagined.

488
00:36:07,064 --> 00:36:08,299
Last but not least,

489
00:36:08,933 --> 00:36:11,335
I'm going to place the paper in the water.

490
00:36:15,106 --> 00:36:17,474
This is how it turned out.

491
00:36:17,475 --> 00:36:18,843
Wow.

492
00:36:19,710 --> 00:36:21,345
Shall we all try it as well?

493
00:36:23,714 --> 00:36:24,615
Sure.

494
00:36:25,249 --> 00:36:26,684
I'll give it a try.

495
00:36:29,654 --> 00:36:31,956
Mrs. Tachibana, you're so good at this.
It's so pretty.

496
00:36:33,457 --> 00:36:34,892
You're doing well too.

497
00:36:35,493 --> 00:36:38,196
Oh no, don't go that way…

498
00:36:41,432 --> 00:36:44,034
At first, I was trying to create a dragon,

499
00:36:44,035 --> 00:36:45,903
but this is how it turned out.

500
00:36:48,606 --> 00:36:52,042
I actually put in a bit too much sumi ink
right at the start,

501
00:36:52,043 --> 00:36:56,414
so I decided to just utilize that
and simply go with the flow.

502
00:36:56,981 --> 00:36:58,349
How did you like it?

503
00:36:59,584 --> 00:37:00,651
Well,

504
00:37:01,219 --> 00:37:03,520
I couldn't control it well enough,

505
00:37:03,521 --> 00:37:04,855
so it was a bit frustrating.

506
00:37:05,423 --> 00:37:06,257
And you, Mrs. Tamami?

507
00:37:07,225 --> 00:37:11,828
It turned out completely differently
than I had imagined,

508
00:37:11,829 --> 00:37:14,465
but that actually
made it all the more fun.

509
00:37:15,032 --> 00:37:18,435
Mr. Yukio approached it with
a clear vision right from the start,

510
00:37:18,436 --> 00:37:20,705
while Mrs. Tamami simply let
the ink take its course.

511
00:37:21,272 --> 00:37:23,140
That contrast is quite fascinating.

512
00:37:24,175 --> 00:37:25,409
How about you, Tatsuki?

513
00:37:27,078 --> 00:37:28,478
With <i>suminagashi</i>,

514
00:37:28,479 --> 00:37:31,548
once you drop the ink, there's no telling
how it's going to spread, huh?

515
00:37:31,549 --> 00:37:34,751
Watching over those
unpredictable movements

516
00:37:34,752 --> 00:37:35,653
is what makes this fun.

517
00:37:37,221 --> 00:37:38,422
But

518
00:37:39,624 --> 00:37:43,361
I guess I was trying to control things
to make it turn out the way I want.

519
00:37:57,008 --> 00:38:01,412
You haven't seen
Nene's diamond art yet, have you?

520
00:38:01,979 --> 00:38:02,813
No.

521
00:38:05,316 --> 00:38:07,751
You mentioned
that she chose brown and pink

522
00:38:07,752 --> 00:38:11,721
because she thought they were colors
that'd make us happy, right?

523
00:38:11,722 --> 00:38:12,590
Yes.

524
00:38:13,658 --> 00:38:16,394
At first, she didn't have the confidence
to choose the colors herself.

525
00:38:17,295 --> 00:38:18,729
What about this foal?

526
00:38:19,597 --> 00:38:23,566
At first it was made with a mix
of brown and pink,

527
00:38:23,567 --> 00:38:25,435
because brown would make her dad happy,

528
00:38:25,436 --> 00:38:27,138
and pink is her mom's favorite color.

529
00:38:28,839 --> 00:38:30,341
But before she could show it to you guys,

530
00:38:30,941 --> 00:38:32,743
she tried to destroy it.

531
00:38:34,178 --> 00:38:37,481
<i>But she brought it with her
to the Yukanai Camp.</i>

532
00:38:38,049 --> 00:38:39,750
I worked so hard to make it,

533
00:38:40,685 --> 00:38:41,986
but I ended up destroying it.

534
00:38:44,789 --> 00:38:48,558
And when she decided to work on it again,

535
00:38:48,559 --> 00:38:51,996
she was finally able to tell me

536
00:38:52,663 --> 00:38:54,165
her favorite color.

537
00:38:59,904 --> 00:39:01,739
The truth is, my favorite color is blue.

538
00:39:03,607 --> 00:39:05,343
<i>As I listened closely,</i>

539
00:39:05,910 --> 00:39:09,380
I gradually began hearing the words

540
00:39:10,514 --> 00:39:13,317
she couldn't bring herself to say
until then.

541
00:39:16,253 --> 00:39:17,722
I see.

542
00:39:20,891 --> 00:39:22,326
Perhaps

543
00:39:23,694 --> 00:39:25,862
we were doing nothing but forcing

544
00:39:25,863 --> 00:39:28,032
our own feelings and expectations
onto her.

545
00:39:29,834 --> 00:39:30,901
Yeah.

546
00:39:35,139 --> 00:39:36,507
We'll try once more

547
00:39:37,341 --> 00:39:38,743
to see Nene eye to eye.

548
00:39:40,311 --> 00:39:41,579
That's wonderful.

549
00:39:42,580 --> 00:39:43,881
I think that's a great idea.

550
00:39:47,151 --> 00:39:50,287
I actually have a suggestion
for the both of you.

551
00:40:03,901 --> 00:40:08,072
NENE

552
00:40:22,286 --> 00:40:25,189
<i>We tried our hand at diamond art too.</i>

553
00:40:26,056 --> 00:40:28,559
<i>The messy part was done by Dad.</i>

554
00:40:29,193 --> 00:40:31,395
<i>Nene, please finish the rest.</i>

555
00:41:13,237 --> 00:41:15,172
NOW ACCEPTING NEW STUDENTS

556
00:41:20,544 --> 00:41:21,512
Good morning Tatsuki.

557
00:41:22,079 --> 00:41:23,647
Good morning.

558
00:41:25,115 --> 00:41:26,317
I decided not to leave.

559
00:41:26,884 --> 00:41:27,718
Huh?

560
00:41:29,019 --> 00:41:31,388
All right!

561
00:41:32,590 --> 00:41:34,525
What should I do today?

562
00:41:41,966 --> 00:41:43,400
What's this?

563
00:41:44,802 --> 00:41:47,203
That's called <i>suminagashi</i>.

564
00:41:47,204 --> 00:41:48,137
- I see.
- Oh.

565
00:41:48,138 --> 00:41:50,006
Do you want to try paper marbling?

566
00:41:50,007 --> 00:41:51,041
What is that?

567
00:41:51,675 --> 00:41:53,910
It's similar to <i>suminagashi</i>
but it uses color ink.

568
00:41:53,911 --> 00:41:55,079
I want to try it.

569
00:42:09,260 --> 00:42:12,662
Your style is so free and relaxed.
It's nice.

570
00:42:12,663 --> 00:42:13,998
- Really?
- Yeah.

571
00:42:17,401 --> 00:42:20,404
How's your dad and mom lately?

572
00:42:21,438 --> 00:42:23,474
We haven't talked about anything yet.

573
00:42:23,974 --> 00:42:25,843
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

574
00:42:26,877 --> 00:42:27,711
I see.

575
00:42:31,615 --> 00:42:34,852
But I think it's going to be okay now.

576
00:42:38,355 --> 00:42:39,189
Okay.

577
00:42:42,226 --> 00:42:43,227
Tatsuki…

578
00:42:45,629 --> 00:42:46,564
Thank you.

579
00:42:49,333 --> 00:42:51,235
- Say that again?
- Never mind.

580
00:42:55,205 --> 00:42:56,874
Tatsuki, do you have a kid?

581
00:42:58,375 --> 00:42:59,643
Yeah.

582
00:43:00,744 --> 00:43:02,580
You have to take good care of your family.

583
00:43:04,682 --> 00:43:07,484
- Why do you say that?
- I just felt like I had to say it.

584
00:43:09,320 --> 00:43:10,154
‎I see.

585
00:43:22,032 --> 00:43:24,101
All right, I'm done.

586
00:43:27,571 --> 00:43:28,606
Pull the paper up.

587
00:43:30,774 --> 00:43:32,475
- Ta-da.
- Wow.

588
00:43:32,476 --> 00:43:33,677
How is it?

589
00:43:34,345 --> 00:43:36,679
- Does it look nice?
- Very nice.

590
00:43:36,680 --> 00:43:37,548
Thanks.

591
00:43:38,315 --> 00:43:39,215
All right.

592
00:43:39,216 --> 00:43:41,285
- It's beautiful.
- So pretty.

593
00:43:41,852 --> 00:43:43,921
- The orange color adds a nice accent.
- Yeah.

594
00:44:16,954 --> 00:44:18,121
I'll be going now.

595
00:44:18,122 --> 00:44:20,089
Bye.

596
00:44:20,090 --> 00:44:20,958
Keep at it.

597
00:44:21,458 --> 00:44:22,493
Thanks.

598
00:44:23,227 --> 00:44:24,128
NOW ACCEPTING NEW STUDENTS

599
00:45:01,965 --> 00:45:02,999
Garbage…

600
00:45:03,000 --> 00:45:03,900
PREVIEW OF THE NEXT EPISODE

601
00:45:03,901 --> 00:45:05,235
…will always be

602
00:45:05,936 --> 00:45:07,637
nothing but garbage.

603
00:45:07,638 --> 00:45:08,872
Subtitle translation by: Lili Morita
